{"id": "752308", "revid": "15881234", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki?curid=752308", "title": "Oudekapelle", "text": "Oudekapelle is a small village in the Belgian province of West Flanders and a part (\"deelgemeente\") of the municipality of Diksmuide. Oudekapelle is a small village with only about ten houses around the church and farms on its territory. It has about 150 inhabitants.\nOudekapelle was an independent municipality until 1971, when it became a part of a newly formed municipality of Driekapellen, together with Nieuwkapelle en Sint-Jacobskapelle. In 1977, Driekapellen itself became a part of Diksmuide."}
