{"id": "752486", "revid": "380601", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki?curid=752486", "title": "Yuri Amano", "text": " is a Japanese voice actress who is affiliated with Arts Vision. Her real name, as well as her former stage name, is . Her best known role is Rain Mikamura in \"Mobile Fighter G Gundam\" and Kiyone Makibi in the \"Tenchi Muyo!\" franchise. Other major roles include Asako Nakamura in \"Ushio and Tora\", Keiko Yukimura in \"YuYu Hakusho\", Alcyone in \"Magic Knight Rayearth\", and Lorelei in the \"Saber Marionette J\" series. In video games, she voices Mary Argent in \"Tales of Destiny\", Hokuto in \"Street Fighter EX\", Ibuki in \"Street Fighter III\", and Etoile Rosenqueen in the \"Marl Kingdom\" series."}
